title: Man United vs St Etienne: Jose Mourinho makes six changes ahead of EFL Cup final | Metro News
text:
Sean Kearns for Metro.co.uk Wednesday 22 Feb 2017 3:54 pm Jose Mourinho’s made six changes to his side (Picture: Getty) 
Jose Mourinho has made six changes to his Manchester United side for their trip to St Etienne. 
The Red Devils take a three-goal lead to France and are the overwhelming favourites to reach the last-16. 
Mourinho’s men must contend with a congested fixture list in the coming weeks and the 54-year-old’s got one eye on Sunday’s EFL Cup final clash against Southampton. 
However the Portuguese boss has selected a very strong side with the likes of Zlatan Ibrahimovic, Paul Pogba and Eric Bailly all starting in France. #MUFC team to face Saint-Etienne: Romero, Young, Smalling, Bailly, Blind, Carrick (c), Pogba, Fellaini, Mata, Mkhitaryan, Ibrahimovic. #UEL 
— Manchester United (@ManUtd) February 22, 2017 
The likes of Antonio Valencia, David De Gea and Anthony Martial have all been named among the substitutes with Mourinho clearly unwilling to take risks against the Ligue 1 side.
